'''Auch'''

The name Auch has two possible origins:

I). Common in Southern Germany as an occupational surname for those whose watched livestock at night, from the middle-high German ''Uhte'', which means "night watch", "night pasture", or "the time just before dawn".

II). Possibly French. Habitational name from the Southern town of [[Auch]].


